# Local Gateway Agent — Cloud-to-Edge Biometric Bridge

## Problem Statement

The CollPoll SaaS platform is hosted in the cloud (Vercel/AWS). Biometric devices (Hikvision) sit on private campus LANs (e.g., `192.168.x.x`). The cloud **cannot** reach private IPs — all `callDeviceProxy` → `digestFetch` calls fail with "Device is unreachable" in production.

**Two distinct networking problems must be solved:**

| # | Direction | Description | Currently Handled By |
|---|-----------|-------------|---------------------|
| 1 | **Cloud → Device** (Outbound Commands) | Register users, sync faces, capture fingerprints, configure webhooks | [device-proxy/route.ts](file:///d:/collpoll_client/app/api/biometric/device-proxy/route.ts) — makes direct HTTP Digest calls to device IP |
| 2 | **Device → Cloud** (Inbound Scan Events) | Device pushes scan logs to our webhook | [scan/route.ts](file:///d:/collpoll_client/app/api/biometric/scan/route.ts) — the device `POST`s to `/api/biometric/scan` |

> [!IMPORTANT]
> **Problem #2 (Inbound Scans) already works in production** IF the campus router does port-forwarding or the device can resolve the public hostname. The Hikvision device pushes outbound HTTP to `tektoncampus.com/api/biometric/scan`, which is publicly reachable. **No changes needed for scan ingestion.**
>
> **Problem #1 (Outbound Commands) is the one that breaks.** This is what the Local Gateway Agent solves.

