## Proposed Changes — Detailed

### Phase 1: Database Schema

#### [NEW] `campus_agents` table

```sql
CREATE TABLE campus_agents (
  agentId          SERIAL PRIMARY KEY,
  collegeId        INTEGER NOT NULL REFERENCES colleges(collegeId),
  agentName        TEXT NOT NULL DEFAULT 'Campus Agent',
  agentSecret      TEXT NOT NULL,  -- Shared secret for auth
  isOnline         BOOLEAN NOT NULL DEFAULT false,
  lastHeartbeat    TIMESTAMPTZ,
  agentVersion     TEXT,
  localIpAddress   TEXT,           -- Agent's LAN IP (for debug)
  createdAt        TIMESTAMPTZ NOT NULL DEFAULT now(),
  updatedAt        TIMESTAMPTZ NOT NULL DEFAULT now(),
  
  UNIQUE(collegeId)  -- One agent per campus
);
```

#### [NEW] `agent_command_queue` table

```sql
CREATE TABLE agent_command_queue (
  commandId        UUID PRIMARY KEY DEFAULT gen_random_uuid(),
  collegeId        INTEGER NOT NULL REFERENCES colleges(collegeId),
  deviceId         INTEGER NOT NULL REFERENCES biometric_devices(deviceId),
  
  -- The exact proxy request payload
  endpoint         TEXT NOT NULL,        -- e.g. "AccessControl/UserInfo/Record"
  method           TEXT NOT NULL DEFAULT 'POST',
  payload          JSONB,               -- The body to send
  contentType      TEXT,                -- e.g. "application/xml"
  isMultipart      BOOLEAN DEFAULT false,
  multipartData    JSONB,               -- Base64-encoded parts for multipart
  
  -- Command lifecycle
  status           TEXT NOT NULL DEFAULT 'pending'
                   CHECK (status IN ('pending', 'processing', 'completed', 'failed', 'expired')),
  result           JSONB,               -- Response from device
  resultHttpStatus INTEGER,             -- HTTP status from device
  errorMessage     TEXT,
  
  -- Timeouts & retries
  createdAt        TIMESTAMPTZ NOT NULL DEFAULT now(),
  pickedUpAt       TIMESTAMPTZ,
  completedAt      TIMESTAMPTZ,
  expiresAt        TIMESTAMPTZ NOT NULL DEFAULT (now() + INTERVAL '60 seconds'),
  retryCount       INTEGER DEFAULT 0,
  maxRetries       INTEGER DEFAULT 2,
  
  updatedAt        TIMESTAMPTZ NOT NULL DEFAULT now()
);

-- Index for agent polling (hot path)
CREATE INDEX idx_agent_queue_pending 
  ON agent_command_queue (collegeId, status, createdAt) 
  WHERE status = 'pending';

-- Auto-expire stale commands (Supabase cron or app-level)
CREATE INDEX idx_agent_queue_expiry
  ON agent_command_queue (expiresAt) 
  WHERE status IN ('pending', 'processing');
```

> [!NOTE]
> **Why a command queue instead of Supabase Realtime broadcast?**
> - Realtime broadcast is fire-and-forget — if the agent misses a message, it's lost forever.
> - A DB queue guarantees delivery, supports retries, and provides a full audit trail.
> - The agent uses Supabase Realtime only as a **notification trigger** ("hey, there's a new command") to avoid polling, but reads the actual command from the DB.

